A man decides to test his willpower by getting addicted to coffee and then overcoming the addiction.

He is successful and attempts the experiment again - this time with cigarettes. Smoking for a period of time and afterwards breaking the dependence off. He proceeds to repeat ...

He has gotten himself addicted to overcoming addictions, he is caught in a primordial trap lying in the depths of everyone's mind: by trying to fight the newfound dependence, he indulges in it. He has turned his brain into a staircase to nowhere. Slowly, he descends into madness.

with other, progressively more dangerous substances: sugar, alcohol, pain medication, cocaine - slowly strengthening his mind, periodically overcoming his lizard brain. Finally - he performs the experiment with heroin and is once again successful.
